The article commemorates the 40th anniversary of St. Pope John Paul II's historic Mass celebration in Warsaw, Poland, on June 2, 1979. It acknowledges the impact of his visit in changing the course of history and the struggle of the Polish people against communism. St. Pope John Paul II's powerful message of hope inspired millions to seek a better and freer life. The article also reaffirms the commitment of the United States and its allies to ensuring that freedom always prevails. Melania Trump joins in remembering St. Pope John Paul II and his role in tearing down the Iron Curtain of communism in Europe.